5: Whew... This sure takes me back.
9:
I guess I shouldn't be surprised you
grew up on a vessel.
13:
Most people in our world live on floats
like this one. Only a small percentage
live on solid ground.
16:
I appreciate you all coming out here,
but as I said, there's not much to see.
20: Are you sure? I wouldn't say that.
25:
Yeah, this is all new to us! Plus, I bet
there's a ton of seafood to try out!
30: Well, I suppose that is true.
33: No way! It's really him, isn't it?
38:
Yes! Rain of the Gaea Naval Academy,
reporting in!
45:
Wh-why are you laughing?! I'll have you
know I am a full-fledged—
48:
D'aww, look at him! Acting like such
a big strong man with his widdle sailor
cappy!
52:
Argh! L-let me go! And stop messing
with my hair!
57: Why are you guys always like this to me!
60: Because you're just so dang adorable!
62:
You're STILL going through with the
whole navy thing?
66:
Of course. That's the reason I left this
place after all.
68:
Aww, laaaame. You should just forget
about that.
71:
They're here again today. You'd better
not turn into another one of them, okay?
75: What did she mean by that?
78:
The people who live here aren't fond of
the Gaean Navy—especially the ones in
uniform.
83:
Well, since you're here, how about
attending a speech?
86:
...Thus, we will continue to rely on the 
support from floatdwellers to identify 
the cause of these rising waters. 
On the other hand...
91:
He's been going on for like an hour now
but hasn't actually said anything.
95:
Well, simply put, we haven't
accomplished any of our goals, but are
asking the residents here to front the
payment.
97:
And if you think an hour was long, this
story's been the same since I was just
a kid.
101:
They're certainly taking their time,
aren't they?
104:
Yeah... I saw a lot of their kind back at
the palace.
107:
They're not bad people—the rank and
file seem to have no complaints about
them at least.
111:
So why did you want to become an
officer?
115:
I mean, we can't let people like that
stay in charge, right?
117:
I've realized during my time as a sailor
that we can't let things stay the way
they are. Someone has to step up and
do something.
120:
And you think that someone will be
you one day?
128:
So we're incompetent is what yer
saying, huh?
131:
This cadet's gonna need a new hat
if his head got any bigger!
138:
Rain, you little rascal! We'll show you
to mouth off about us all the time!
141:
Hey, ow! Not the hair—I mean, get your
hands off of me!
145: Uh, do you know these people?
150:
Ah, hello there. Thanks for watching
over our cheeky little friend.
154:
Oh, certainly. Rain's been a huge help
to us.
157:
Yeah, he's a real helper, ain't he?
You don't see a lotta sailors gunnin'
to be officers.
158:
Cuz of that, he's got all sorts of eyes
on him at the academy. I suppose that's
nothin' new for him though.
159:
I'm tellin' ya, people are obsessed
with the guy!
163:
I suppose he is quite an impressive
character.
166:
By the way, I'm the president of the
Rain fan club.
169: I'm sorry, but I'm not sure I follow.
172:
We're all waitin' to see him graduate,
but there's a bit of a problem, you see...
174:
The kid's a bit slow, right? I mean, you'd
never guess by lookin' at him.
182:
It does seem that he isn't quite
equipped for classroom-style learning.
188: But that's all right—I'll see what I can do.
197: I'll do whatever I can to help too!
208:
You could start by cutting the chit-chat
and helping me already!
